# Caching & CDN Spec

## Scope

HTTP cache headers, CDN-safe page flows, static/upload caching, and generated
nginx cache behavior.

## Load when

Changing `utils.WriteJSON`, nginx generation, uploads/static serving, page route
resolution, SSR, or CDN-facing behavior.

## Owns

- API cache headers: `backend/internal/utils/http.go`
- Runtime nginx generator: `internal/app/nginx.go`
- Frontend image nginx variant: `backend/frontend/nginx/default.conf`
- Page flow: `.specs/route_resolution_spec`

## Contracts

| Layer | Contract |
| --- | --- |
| Go JSON APIs | `Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate` and `Pragma: no-cache` |
| Generated nginx API/config paths | no-store cache headers |
| `/uploads/*` | `public, max-age=2592000` (30 days) |
| Vite assets | hashed filenames; immutable-style static caching |
| WebSocket | not cacheable; upgrade proxied at `/ws` and `/api/ws` |
| SSR HTML | may be rewritten with SEO/site config; avoid relying on CDN purge for correctness |

## CDN-Safe Page Pattern

Landing page cold load must use:

1. `GET /pages/landing-slug`
2. `GET /pages/{slug}`

Reason: `/pages/index` is a single cache key that can point at different pages
over time. Per-slug fetches keep URL and resource identity aligned.

Live page changes bypass CDN through WebSocket:

- `page:update landing_page_changed` carries the full page.
- `page:update page_updated` carries the full page.
- `config:update landing_page_updated` carries `{ slug }` as a fallback/UI signal.

## Anti-patterns

- Returning different resources from the same cacheable URL.
- Redirecting API endpoints for correctness.
- Relying on Cloudflare purge to make live data correct.
- Editing generated nginx config instead of `internal/app/nginx.go`.

## Verify

- `rg "Cache-Control|Pragma|no-store" backend internal main.go router.go -n`
- `rg "landing-slug|pages/index|landing_page_changed" backend backend/frontend .specs -n`

## Trace

- `.specs/route_resolution_spec`
- `.specs/infrastructure_spec`
